$ Stellarium API: setDate

code {
core.setDate(
  date              ,  //  date
  spec              ,  // "utc" or "local"
  deltaTCorrection     //  A flag/boolean if → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/Delta-T[Delta-T] correction should be applied
)
code }

`date` can be specified
   • in → misc/ISO/8601[ISO 8601] format, for example `"yyyy-mm-ddThh:mi:ss"`
   • relatively, for example `"+ 4 days"` (with or without `sidereal`). Units must always be plural.
   • to `"now"`

{ Example

  gh|about-Stellarium|/API/core/setDate.ssc||

}

sa:

  `core.getDate()` returns the current simulation time in → misc/ISO/8601[ISO 8601] format.

  → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium/script/API
